        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="828" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d828">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/12–2945: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-29">December 29,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received January 15, 1946—2:49 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–175. Continuing Legation’s telegram no. 515 of December 28, 3 p.m. Fadhil
                    Jamali, Director General of Foreign Office, states that customary note of
                    protest has not been sent to Legation regarding Congressional resolutions
                    favoring Zionism because 1) full text of resolutions not yet obtained by Foreign
                    Ministry; and because 2) Nuri Pasha, who is usually consulted on such matters,
                    has been out of country. Dr. Jamali assures Legation that protest will be made
                    in due course.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
